docs/DECISIONS.md:9:This replaces the previous "choose one of owner brief / CI triage / task loop" milestone framing. Owner briefs, CI triage, PR readiness, handoffs, packets, and archives remain useful only as parts of end-to-end task execution.
docs/DECISIONS.md:54:Packets, viewers, archives, handoffs, schemas, lifecycle reports, and setup policies are implementation capabilities. They are not product goals.
docs/DECISIONS.md:62:Do not start Alpha-28, new archive/viewer work, new handoff/audit features, new OKF/skills lifecycle work, or new safety layers before `TASK-RUN-1`.
docs/alpha-snapshot-2026-07-02.md:13:- leave the final apply decision to a human reviewer.
docs/alpha-snapshot-2026-07-02.md:39:`proposal-status.json` is the machine-readable outcome record. `patch-summary.md` and `human-review.md` are reviewer-facing. `proposal.patch` is a proposal artifact only; a human may apply it manually outside RunForge after review.
docs/alpha-snapshot-2026-07-02.md:71:- Improve reviewer ergonomics in the packet before adding hosting or automation.
