docs/engineering-rules.md:8:   - Checks must not require network services, hosted mode, SaaS infrastructure, BYOC setup, dashboards, billing, marketplaces, persona reviewers, auto-fix flows, workflow engines, or self-improvement overlays.
docs/engineering-rules.md:31:   - Agents inspect branch, status, and base commit before work, stage explicit paths, avoid destructive git operations without approval, and report status, diff summary, checks, and commit hash at handoff.
docs/demo-walkthrough.md:20:Start with `human-review.md`. It is the reviewer entry point and explains what task was attempted, which context was collected, which checks were used, which patch is proposed, why the packet is safe, whether the repo changed, and what a human should do next.
docs/packet-schema.md:189:- `proposal-status.json.reviewerDecision`: deterministic reviewer decision
docs/packet-schema.md:213:- Expected deterministic code proposal worker roles are `readiness_loader`, `context_scout`, `failure_analyst`, `proposal_planner`, `patch_writer`, `verifier`, `proposal_reviewer`, and `packet_writer`.
docs/packet-schema.md:214:- Provider-backed packets also emit `provider_input_builder`, `provider_runner`, `provider_patch_validator`, and `provider_safety_reviewer`.
